sentences: St. Clair Pinckney (September 17, 1930 – February 1, 1999) was an American saxophonist who performed with James Brown as a member of the James Brown Orchestra and The J.B.'s.
Suffering from health issues for years, Pinckney left Brown's band in 1999.
